    <h5 class="ppolicy2">Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before using this website.</h5>
    <p class="ppolicy2">Thank you for visiting our website, owned and operated by American Life Coverage (“<span style="letter-spacing: -0.27px;">American Life Coverage</span>”, “we”, “us”, “our”). “<span style="letter-spacing: -0.27px;">American Life Coverage</span>”, “we”, “us”, and “our” for purposes of this Privacy Policy refers only to&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: -0.27px;">American Life Coverage</span>I and its subsidiaries, and to not our parent company Prudential Financial or any of its other subsidiaries.&nbsp;<span style="letter-spacing: -0.27px;">American Life Coverage&nbsp;</span>is here to protect and improve the personal and financial health of all consumers. Before you use this website and our other services—which include, among other things, collecting information from you in order to generate insurance and other financial product quotes and to connect you with insurance agents and other financial services professionals to discuss your needs (our website and these and other services are referred to collectively as the “Services”)—we’d like to tell you more about the information we collect about you and what we do with it.</p>
    <p class="ppolicy2">When you use, access or interact with our services (for example, by inputting your information on this website), you are agreeing to our&nbsp;<a class="op" href="{{ route('terms')}}">Terms of Service</a>&nbsp;and also consenting to how we collect, share and otherwise use information about you as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>
